Hyundai Motor Plans $173 Million Alabama Engine Line Expansion

-- B y   A l a n   O h n s m a n
-- 
2011-05-16T17:33:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/hyundai-motor-plans-173-million-alabama-engine-line-expansion.html
Hyundai Motor Co. (005380) , South Korea’s
biggest carmaker, plans to spend $173 million and create 214
jobs to expand and upgrade its Alabama manufacturing site to
produce more four-cylinder engines.  The company intends to build its 1.8-liter “Nu” engine at
the Montgomery factory starting in March 2012, Robert Burns, the
plant’s spokesman, said today in an interview. The motors will
be used in Elantra compact cars built in Montgomery, he said.  Hyundai’s U.S. sales unit is based in  Fountain Valley ,
California.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Ohnsman in Los Angeles at 
 aohnsman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kae Inoue at 
 kinoue@bloomberg.net  